    "name": "Special Topics in Bioengineering; Systems Medicine",
    "credits": "3",
    "description": "Prerequisites: MATH246 and BIOE232; or students who have taken courses with comparable content may contact the department. Students will learn the fundamentals of a physiological system, then create simple basic principles or laws to explain why the system is built the way it is. why it goes wrong or becomes pathologic, and which new strategies might treat them. In particular, we will study diabetes, autoimmune diseases, lung fibrosis, and cancer."
